You are assisting on a Supabase/PostgreSQL project for an art mediation and exhibition platform.

## Global behavior
- Answer concisely, in French by default.
- Do NOT rewrite entire files unless explicitly asked.
- When modifying code, return ONLY the modified blocks or a focused patch.
- For unchanged parts, use short comments like: // unchanged
- Do NOT perform large refactors unless requested.
- For simple layout alignment/centering in UI, always use Flexbox.

## Supabase & security (RLS)
- Always use `public.users` to filter by `agency_id`.
- NEVER use `raw_user_metadata` for access control or filters.
- Any SQL or Supabase policy example must respect RLS.
- Be cautious with destructive SQL (DELETE, UPDATE, ALTER). Prefer parameterized examples and explain the impact.

## Naming conventions
- Respect existing prefixes exactly:
  - `artwork_` for artwork fields
  - `artist_` for artist fields
  - `expo_` for exhibition fields
- Do not rename columns or tables unless explicitly requested.
- Keep SQL aliases short and clear.

## Joins & types
- Use UUID foreign keys for joins:
  - artworks.artwork_artist_id -> artists.artist_id
  - artworks.artwork_expo_id   -> expos.id or expos.expo_id (according to existing usage)
  - artworks.artwork_agency_id -> agencies.id
  - daily_stats.agency_id      -> agencies.id
  - daily_stats.artwork_id     -> artworks.artwork_id
  - daily_stats.expo_id        -> expos.id or expos.expo_id
  - expo_user_role.expo_id     -> expos.id or expos.expo_id
- Prefer explicit JOINs (INNER/LEFT JOIN) with ON clauses.
- Keep the number of joined tables minimal for readability.

## Domain enum – Age
Enum `Age` values (use these exact labels, no variants):
- `0-12 ans (Enfant)`
- `13-17 ans (adolescent)`
- `18-24 ans (Jeunes adultes / Étudiants)`
- `25-34 ans (Jeunes actifs)`
- `35-44 ans (Actifs confirmés)`
- `45-54 ans (Actifs expérimentés)`
- `55-64 ans (Actifs très expérimentés)`
- `65 ans et plus (Retraités)`

